    whyItMatters: 'Apple is the most important case study in design-driven innovation and brand building. It proves that premium pricing can coexist with mass-market adoption — the iPhone has 50%+ smartphone market share in the US despite costing 2-3x more than Android alternatives. Apple demonstrates that focusing on user experience can trump specifications and features. The company\'s vertical integration strategy (designing its own chips, operating system, and hardware) has become a model that competitors like Google and Microsoft are now emulating. Apple also shows how a services transition can create a second growth curve — services now generate more profit than the entire Fortune 500 company.',
