    whyItMatters: 'Google is the default gateway to the internet — it decides what information people find and what businesses succeed online. The company\'s rise from a Stanford project to a $1.5 trillion company in 25 years is the defining story of the internet era. Google\'s advertising model (pay-per-click auctions) replaced the entire advertising industry (newspapers, Yellow Pages, radio) and created a $600+ billion digital advertising market. Google\'s corporate structure (Alphabet) and "moonshot" culture (self-driving cars, balloon internet, life sciences) represents a new model for how technology companies should manage innovation at scale. For business students, Google is the ultimate case study in platform businesses, network effects, and the economics of data.',
