    whyItMatters: 'Microsoft\'s story is the most important case study in corporate reinvention. The company that missed the internet, mobile, and search — arguably the three biggest tech shifts of the 1995-2010 period — somehow became one of the most valuable companies in the world again. Satya Nadella\'s transformation is studied in business schools as a masterclass in changing corporate culture, strategy, and business model. Microsoft demonstrates: (1) The power of the installed base — Microsoft\'s existing enterprise relationships were a distribution advantage that AWS and Google could not match. (2) The importance of embracing platforms — Microsoft\'s shift from selling software to selling cloud subscriptions transformed its revenue predictability and valuation multiples. (3) The value of strategic partnerships — the OpenAI partnership positioned Microsoft as the leader in enterprise AI without the risk of building foundational models from scratch.',
